cdx6500GCTLANConnectionTable.name: cdx6500GCTLANConnectionTable
cdx6500GCTLANConnectionTable.description: A list of parameters for configuring LAN Connections.

cdx6500GCTLANConnectionEntry.name: cdx6500GCTLANConnectionEntry
cdx6500GCTLANConnectionEntry.description: Each entry contains the Configuration parameters for each LAN Connection.

cdx6500WAEntryNumber.name: cdx6500WAEntryNumber
cdx6500WAEntryNumber.description: This is a standard table entry number. It identifies a specific LAN Connection Record within the table.

cdx6500WALanForwarderType.name: cdx6500WALanForwarderType
cdx6500WALanForwarderType.description: This parameter specifies the type of forwarders communicating over this LAN Connection. brid - Bridging Forwarders. rout - Routing Forwarders. brout - Bridging and Routing Forwarders. nc - Skipped during configuration. newvalBrid - same functionality as 'brid', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500WABridgeLinkNumber.name: cdx6500WABridgeLinkNumber
cdx6500WABridgeLinkNumber.description: This parameter specifies the Bridge-Link that is using this LAN Connection.

cdx6500WARouterInterfaceNum.name: cdx6500WARouterInterfaceNum
cdx6500WARouterInterfaceNum.description: This parameter specifies the Router Interface that is using this LAN Connection.

cdx6500WACfgEncapsulationType.name: cdx6500WACfgEncapsulationType
cdx6500WACfgEncapsulationType.description: This parameter specifies the data encapsulation type used over this LAN Connection. This object has been deprecated, use cdx6500WACfgEncapType instead.

cdx6500WAAutocallMnemonic.name: cdx6500WAAutocallMnemonic
cdx6500WAAutocallMnemonic.description: If configured, the Autocall Mnemonic references a remote address which will be called by the LAN Connection.

cdx6500WAAutocallTimeout.name: cdx6500WAAutocallTimeout
cdx6500WAAutocallTimeout.description: This is the time interval in seconds between call attempts when auto calling.

cdx6500WAMaxAutocallAttempts.name: cdx6500WAMaxAutocallAttempts
cdx6500WAMaxAutocallAttempts.description: This parameter is used to specify the number of times that the LAN Connection will attempt to autocall a remote destination. A value of zero will allow unlimited attempts.

cdx6500WARemoteConnectionId.name: cdx6500WARemoteConnectionId
cdx6500WARemoteConnectionId.description: This parameter specifies the number of the remote LAN Connection or the FRA Station number that this LAN connection will attempt to connect to if configured for autocall.

cdx6500WABillingRecords.name: cdx6500WABillingRecords
cdx6500WABillingRecords.description: This controls whether billing (accounting) records will be created for calls on this LAN Connection. off : Billing records will not be created. on : Billing records will be created. nc : Skipped during configuration. newvalOff : same functionality as 'off', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500WADataPassingPriority.name: cdx6500WADataPassingPriority
cdx6500WADataPassingPriority.description: This parameter specifies the Traffic Priority of this LAN Connection. low - Low Priority. med - Medium Priority. high - High Priority. exp - Expedite Priority. nc - Skipped during configuration. newvalLow - same functionality as 'low', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500WALCONQueueLimit.name: cdx6500WALCONQueueLimit
cdx6500WALCONQueueLimit.description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of bytes that will be queued for this LCON befor transmission on the WAN link. It is recommended that this parameter be set for two seconds of data on the WAN link.

cdx6500WACfgEncapType.name: cdx6500WACfgEncapType
cdx6500WACfgEncapType.description: This parameter specifies the data encapsulation type used over this LAN Connection. codex - Codex Proprietary Encapsulation. rfc1294 - RFC 1294 Multiprotocol Encapsulation. rfc877 - RFC 877 Multiprotocol Encapsulation. nc - Skipped during configuration. newvalCodex - same functionality as 'codex', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500WACfgOnDemand.name: cdx6500WACfgOnDemand
cdx6500WACfgOnDemand.description: This parameter controls whether the circuit is established at startup or established when required for data passing. disabled - Circuit is established at start up. enabled - Circuit is established on demand. nc - Skipped during configuration. newvalDisabled - same functionality as 'disabled', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500WACfgIdleTimeout.name: cdx6500WACfgIdleTimeout
cdx6500WACfgIdleTimeout.description: This parameter specifies the amount of time in seconds the circuit will remain connected without passing any data before being brought down. Setting the parameter to zero keeps the circuit up indefinitely

cdx6500WACfgLanConnectionType.name: cdx6500WACfgLanConnectionType
cdx6500WACfgLanConnectionType.description: This parameter specifies whether the LAN Connection defines a point to point connection across the WAN, or is part of a group of LAN Connections. ptToPt - Point to Point LAN Connection. group - Member of a LAN Connection Group. nc - Skipped during configuration. newvalPtToPt - same functionality as 'ptToPt', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500WACfgNexthopIpAddress.name: cdx6500WACfgNexthopIpAddress
cdx6500WACfgNexthopIpAddress.description: This parameter specifies the IP address of the Router Interface on the other end of this LAN Connection, which is the next hop on the path to the final destination. A setting of 0.0.0.0 causes this parameter to be ignored.

cdx6500WACfgNexthopIpxNodeNumber.name: cdx6500WACfgNexthopIpxNodeNumber
cdx6500WACfgNexthopIpxNodeNumber.description: This parameter specifies the IPX node number of the Router on the other end of this LAN Connection, which is the next hop on the path to the final destination. A setting of 0 causes this parameter to be ignored.

cdx6500WACfgParallelSvc.name: cdx6500WACfgParallelSvc
cdx6500WACfgParallelSvc.description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of parallel connections that can be established to the remote destination. Parallel SVCs are established when congestion thresholds are reached on active connections.

cdx6500WACfgParallelThreshold.name: cdx6500WACfgParallelThreshold
cdx6500WACfgParallelThreshold.description: This parameter specifies the number of outstanding data bytes that will trigger the establishment of a Parallel SVC. If this number of data bytes has been transmitted without acknowledgment, the receipt of additional data for transmission will trigger Parallel SVC establishment. Note that this parameter must be configured with a value less than the LCON Queue Limit parameter.

cdx6500WACfgParallelPort.name: cdx6500WACfgParallelPort
cdx6500WACfgParallelPort.description: This parameter specifies the port that Parallel SVCs should be brought up over. The parameter can be in two forms. It can be in the form of a port identifier string. For example, to bring Parallel SVCs up over X25 port number 8, enter the string X25-8. It can also be in the form of a Switched Services Table destination name, if the port that the Parallel SVCs are to come up over is a dial on demand port. A value of (blank) will cause Parallel SVCs to be brought up over the same port as the main connection.

cdx6500WACfgBroadcast.name: cdx6500WACfgBroadcast
cdx6500WACfgBroadcast.description: This parameter specifies whether broadcast datagrams should be transmitted over this LAN Connection to the remote destination. disabled : Broadcast datagrams will not be transmitted over this LAN Connection. enabled : Broadcast datagrams will be transmitted over this LAN Connection. nc : Skipped during configuration. newvalDisabled : same functionality as 'disabled', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500GCMaxLCON.name: cdx6500GCMaxLCON
cdx6500GCMaxLCON.description: Defines the maximum number of LAN Connections that may be configured.

cdx6500LCTDataSummaryStats.name: cdx6500LCTDataSummaryStats
cdx6500LCTDataSummaryStats.description: Data summary statstics provides the information on data packets transmitted, received, queued and discarded.

cdx6500WALanConnNumberData.name: cdx6500WALanConnNumberData
cdx6500WALanConnNumberData.description: It identifies a specific LAN Connection Record.

cdx6500WALastStatResetTime.name: cdx6500WALastStatResetTime
cdx6500WALastStatResetTime.description: The date and time of the last statistics reset.

cdx6500WAAvgPktSizeTx.name: cdx6500WAAvgPktSizeTx
cdx6500WAAvgPktSizeTx.description: Specifies the average size of the packets sent on the WAN, in bytes.

cdx6500WACurTxQueueDepth.name: cdx6500WACurTxQueueDepth
cdx6500WACurTxQueueDepth.description: Specifies the current number of packets queued awaiting transmission on the WAN, in packets.

cdx6500WAMaxTxQueueDepth.name: cdx6500WAMaxTxQueueDepth
cdx6500WAMaxTxQueueDepth.description: Specifies the maximum number of packets queued awaiting transmission on the WAN, in packets.

cdx6500WAMaxTxQDepthTime.name: cdx6500WAMaxTxQDepthTime
cdx6500WAMaxTxQDepthTime.description: The date and time when the number of packets queued awaiting transmission on the WAN reached its maximum.

cdx6500WAAvgPktSizeRcv.name: cdx6500WAAvgPktSizeRcv
cdx6500WAAvgPktSizeRcv.description: Specifies the average size of the packets received on the WAN, in bytes.

cdx6500WATxPktDiscardTransDelay.name: cdx6500WATxPktDiscardTransDelay
cdx6500WATxPktDiscardTransDelay.description: Specifies the number of packets discarded due to packets exceeding the maximum allowed delay through the node.

cdx6500WATxPktDiscardCong.name: cdx6500WATxPktDiscardCong
cdx6500WATxPktDiscardCong.description: Specifies the number of packets discarded due to severe congestion.

cdx6500WATxPktDiscardMaxFrame.name: cdx6500WATxPktDiscardMaxFrame
cdx6500WATxPktDiscardMaxFrame.description: Specifies the number of packets discarded due to packets exceeding the maximum allowed frame size.

cdx6500WATxPktDiscardCLrReq.name: cdx6500WATxPktDiscardCLrReq
cdx6500WATxPktDiscardCLrReq.description: Specifies the number of packets discarded due to Clear Requests Received.

cdx6500WATxPktDiscardCallEstab.name: cdx6500WATxPktDiscardCallEstab
cdx6500WATxPktDiscardCallEstab.description: Specifies the number of packets discarded due to Call Establishment Failure.

cdx6500LCTCallSummaryStats.name: cdx6500LCTCallSummaryStats
cdx6500LCTCallSummaryStats.description: A list of Call Summary Statistics for LAN connection.

cdx6500WALanConnNumberCall.name: cdx6500WALanConnNumberCall
cdx6500WALanConnNumberCall.description: It identifies a specific LAN Connection Record.

cdx6500WAConnectionType.name: cdx6500WAConnectionType
cdx6500WAConnectionType.description: Specifies whether the connection is a Permanent Virtual Circuit (PVC) or a Switched Virtual Circuit (SVC).

cdx6500WAStatEncapsulationType.name: cdx6500WAStatEncapsulationType
cdx6500WAStatEncapsulationType.description: This parameter specifies the data encapsulation type used over this LAN Connection. codex - Codex Proprietary Encapsulation. rfc1294 - RFC 1294 Multiprotocol Encapsulation. rfc877 - RFC 877 Multiprotocol Encapsulation. newvalCodex - same functionality as 'codex', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500WAConnectionState.name: cdx6500WAConnectionState
cdx6500WAConnectionState.description: Specifies the current state of the Permanent Virtual Circuit (PVC) or a Switched Virtual Circuit (SVC). unconfigured : Init state. backinHeap : LCONCB has been returned to memory heap. notConnected : Completed Init, waiting for startup, or failed autocall SVC. disabled : Connection is Disabled. calling : Autocall SVC trying to complete call. waitForCall : Non-autocall SVC waiting for call. handshaking : PVC in reset handshake process. connected : Connection is established. connectedCongested : Connection has reached congestion thresh. wfccRecall : Wait for Clr Conf Re-Call, autocall SVC. wfccWaitForCall : Wait for Clr Conf Wait for Call non-auto : calling SVC. wfccDisabled : Wait for Clr Conf goto Disabled. newvalUnconfigured : same functionality as 'unconfigured', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500WAForwardersConnected.name: cdx6500WAForwardersConnected
cdx6500WAForwardersConnected.description: Specifies which forwarders are currently connected to this LAN Connection .

cdx6500WARemoteAddress.name: cdx6500WARemoteAddress
cdx6500WARemoteAddress.description: Specifies the called address of the remote WAN Adaptor LAN Connection for connected SVCs.

cdx6500WANumAutocallAttempts.name: cdx6500WANumAutocallAttempts
cdx6500WANumAutocallAttempts.description: Specifies the number of times attempted to autocall before either succeeded or failed in establishing the connection.

cdx6500WALastClearCauseCode.name: cdx6500WALastClearCauseCode
cdx6500WALastClearCauseCode.description: This is the cause code in the call clear packet last received by the LAN connection and explains why the last call was cleared.

cdx6500WALastClearDiagCode.name: cdx6500WALastClearDiagCode
cdx6500WALastClearDiagCode.description: This is the diagnostic code in the call clear packet last received by the LAN connection and explains why the last call was cleared.

cdx6500WAParallelSvcsEstab.name: cdx6500WAParallelSvcsEstab
cdx6500WAParallelSvcsEstab.description: Count of parallel SVCs with calls established.

cdx6500LCTPacketSummaryStats.name: cdx6500LCTPacketSummaryStats
cdx6500LCTPacketSummaryStats.description: A list of Packet Summary Statistics for LAN connection.

cdx6500WALanConnNumberPkt.name: cdx6500WALanConnNumberPkt
cdx6500WALanConnNumberPkt.description: It identifies a specific LAN Connection Record.

cdx6500WADataPktTx.name: cdx6500WADataPktTx
cdx6500WADataPktTx.description: Specifies the total number of Data Packets sent on the WAN.

cdx6500WADataPktRcv.name: cdx6500WADataPktRcv
cdx6500WADataPktRcv.description: Specifies the total number of Data Packets received from the WAN.

cdx6500WACallReqPktsTx.name: cdx6500WACallReqPktsTx
cdx6500WACallReqPktsTx.description: Specifies the total number of Call Request Packets sent on the WAN.

cdx6500WACallReqPktsRcv.name: cdx6500WACallReqPktsRcv
cdx6500WACallReqPktsRcv.description: Specifies the total number of Call Request Packets received from the WAN.

cdx6500WACallAcceptPktsTx.name: cdx6500WACallAcceptPktsTx
cdx6500WACallAcceptPktsTx.description: Specifies the total number of Call Accept Packets sent on the WAN.

cdx6500WACallAcceptPktsRcv.name: cdx6500WACallAcceptPktsRcv
cdx6500WACallAcceptPktsRcv.description: Specifies the total number of Call Accept Packets received from the WAN.

cdx6500WAClearReqPktsTx.name: cdx6500WAClearReqPktsTx
cdx6500WAClearReqPktsTx.description: Specifies the total number of Clear Request Packets sent on the WAN.

cdx6500WAClearReqPktsRcv.name: cdx6500WAClearReqPktsRcv
cdx6500WAClearReqPktsRcv.description: Specifies the total number of Clear Request Packets received from the WAN.

cdx6500WAClearConfPktsTx.name: cdx6500WAClearConfPktsTx
cdx6500WAClearConfPktsTx.description: Specifies the total number of Clear Confirm Packets sent on the WAN.

cdx6500WAClearConfPktsRcv.name: cdx6500WAClearConfPktsRcv
cdx6500WAClearConfPktsRcv.description: Specifies the total number of Clear Confirm Packets received from the WAN.

cdx6500WAResetReqPktsTx.name: cdx6500WAResetReqPktsTx
cdx6500WAResetReqPktsTx.description: Specifies the total number of Reset Request Packets sent on the WAN.

cdx6500WAResetReqPktsRcv.name: cdx6500WAResetReqPktsRcv
cdx6500WAResetReqPktsRcv.description: Specifies the total number of Reset Request Packets received from the WAN.

cdx6500WAResetConfPktsTx.name: cdx6500WAResetConfPktsTx
cdx6500WAResetConfPktsTx.description: Specifies the total number of Reset Confirm Packets sent on the WAN.

cdx6500WAResetConfPktsRcv.name: cdx6500WAResetConfPktsRcv
cdx6500WAResetConfPktsRcv.description: Specifies the total number of Reset Confirm Packets received from the WAN.

cdx6500ContWANAdaptorTable.name: cdx6500ContWANAdaptorTable
cdx6500ContWANAdaptorTable.description: Control parameters for the LAN Connection.

cdx6500ContWANAdaptorEntry.name: cdx6500ContWANAdaptorEntry
cdx6500ContWANAdaptorEntry.description: Each control applies to a single LAN Connection.

cdx6500WAControlLanConnNumber.name: cdx6500WAControlLanConnNumber
cdx6500WAControlLanConnNumber.description: This identifies a specific LAN Connection Record.

cdx6500WALanConnEnableDisable.name: cdx6500WALanConnEnableDisable
cdx6500WALanConnEnableDisable.description: This command enables or disables a specified LAN connection. newvalEnable : same functionality as 'enable', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500WALanConnBoot.name: cdx6500WALanConnBoot
cdx6500WALanConnBoot.description: This command causes the LAN connection record to be booted.

cdx6500WALanConnResetStat.name: cdx6500WALanConnResetStat
cdx6500WALanConnResetStat.description: When this command is entered the resettable statistics parameters are reset for the specified LAN Connection Number.
